ctives of alumni and current students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aMedical collegesxHistoryxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aMedical collegeszNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aMedicine.  aMount.  aSinais.  aTeaching.  aToday.  aTomorrows.  aaddition.  aboth.  acompelling.  adepartments.  adescribes.  aeach.  aeducation.  agraduate.  ahistory.  amethods.  aphysician.  apost-graduate.  aproviding.  aresident.  aschools.  atraining.1 aJr., Arthur H. Aufses,, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814759127423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814759127/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK